### 4. TanStack Query Caching & Loop Avoidance (Web Frontend)

To solve the infinite fetching loops and recursive rerender triggers on the Next.js frontend, we will integrate TanStack Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) as the centralized data-fetching cache layer.

#### [NEW] [ReactQueryProvider.tsx](file:///c:/Users/evane/OneDrive/Dokumen/Punya%20Ahmad/perpustakaandigital_backup/perpustakaandigital/frontend/src/components/providers/ReactQueryProvider.tsx)
Create a wrapper client provider with safe configurations:
```typescript
'use client';
import { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { ReactNode, useState } from 'react';

export default function ReactQueryProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  const [queryClient] = useState(() => new QueryClient({
    defaultOptions: {
      queries: {
        staleTime: 1000 * 60 * 5, // 5 minutes cache validity
        gcTime: 1000 * 60 * 10,   // 10 minutes garbage collection
        refetchOnWindowFocus: false, // Prevent excessive refetching
        retry: 1,
      },
    },
  }));

  return (
    <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>
      {children}
    </QueryClientProvider>
  );
}
```

